summer of 49, I spent down here. And I got an

16:12.542 --> 16:15.325
enormous amount done in this period. I built an 
apparatus for measuring heat flow down here,

16:16.013 --> 16:27.367
working with Art Maxwell, who's now Deputy 
Director of Woods Hole, and who was then a graduate

16:16.013 --> 16:27.367
student here. And it's interesting looking back 
that there was not enough workshop effort to get

16:28.489 --> 16:35.758
the machine built. It wasn't a very complicated 
thing. And so I said that Maxwell and I would build

16:39.483 --> 16:43.067
it, and we worked in the workshop. And I spent a good 
deal of the summer working in the workshop here,

16:43.722 --> 16:49.830
making this apparatus, which we just got finished 
at the end. We didn't get any measurements with it

16:49.910 --> 16:52.253
that summer. But we got it built, and we showed that 
it would work, and everything was all right. And I

16:56.839 --> 16:59.002
went home and built another one, and that gave 
measurements. And Maxwell built another one

16:59.082 --> 17:03.688
here, slightly different, and that worked. So I 
did that that summer. I also wrote a long paper on

17:05.831 --> 17:13.020
the Earth's magnetic field, on the westward drift 
